<HEADLINE>
FT  04 FEB 92 / International Capital Markets: Surge in net income at BZ
Bank
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By IAN RODGER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   ZURICH
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
BZ BANK, the vehicle for Mr Martin Ebner's aggressive activity in the Swiss
stock markets, reported a 153 per cent rise in its net income last year to
SFr25.1m (Dollars 17.8m), writes Ian Rodger in Zurich.
The seven-year-old bank made gross income of SFr114.9m, up 12.9 per cent, of
which SFr73.3m came from commissions, which advanced 20 per cent. The bank
said brokerage fees contributed about two thirds of the commissions with
underwriting commissions providing the rest.
Total assets surged 39 per cent to SFr506.3m due to higher current loans and
a higher inventory of securities.
</TEXT>
