FT  03 FEB 92 / Female condom nears US approval
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
A CONDOM for women patented by Chartex International, a London-based
unquoted company, has been recommended for approval by a sub-committee of
the US Food and Drug Administration, subject to a contraceptive efficacy
study.
The condom, known as Femidom in Europe and Reality in the US, is a pliable
polyurethane sheath. It will be launched in Switzerland this week. A UK
launch is planned for this summer.
Chartex, has licensed Wisconsin Pharmacal, a Chicago-based group, to
manufacture and market the product in the US.
Femidom has been tested clinically 30,000 times by 1,700 couples in 15
countries.
