FT  03 FEB 92 / Rise found in venture funding
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
LOCAL-AUTHORITY pension funds have become the largest source of venture
capital in the regions, according to a survey by Pensions Investment
Research Consultants (PIRC).
Over two years the funds have increased their investment in venture capital
by 51 per cent to Pounds 271m, PIRC says. This was in a period when the
venture capital industry experienced a general slowdown in rates of growth.
PIRC, which advises local authorities on investments, found that a total of
62 local-authority pension funds, 63 per cent of the total, had made venture
capital investments.
Local Authority Pension Fund Venture Capital Investment. PIRC, 40 Bowling
Green Lane, London EC1R 0NE.
