FT  03 FEB 92 / Lenders see drop in mortgage arrears
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DAVID BARCHARD
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
A FALL in the number of mortgage arrears and of house repossessions has been
well under way since the third quarter of last year, according to the
Council of Mortgage Lenders, David Barchard writes.
A group of mortgage lenders met the council last week and was given
preliminary details of the numbers of repossessions last year. The figures
are to be formally announced on Thursday next week.
Although two lenders have yet to submit their final figures, it seems clear
that the total repossessions last year were well below the 85,000 originally
forecast. The final total could be about 80,000.
Lenders have also been told that the number of accounts between three and
six months in arrears began to fall sharply from last autumn.
