FT  03 FEB 92 / International Company News: Sanyo slips 3.8% despite sales
rise
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By EMIKO TERAZONO
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
SANYO Electric, the Japanese electronics maker, announced a rise of 12.5 per
cent in consolidated pre-tax profits, to Y39.9bn (Dollars 324.4m) for the
year to November, 1991. The result was struck on a 7.8 per cent rise in
sales, to Y1,587.1bn, writes Emiko Terazono.
Operating profit rose only 1.9 per cent to Y49.5bn, due to increased
competition and foreign exchange losses caused by the yen's sharp rise
against the dollar. After-tax profit fell 3.8 per cent to Y16.8bn due to
increased corporate taxes.
