first-half operating losses from Pounds 15m to Pounds 8.8m, although there
was no improvement in trading conditions.
Sales were down 11 per cent at Pounds 99.9m.
While senior lenders are continuing to support Airedale, the company faces a
claim from GE Capital, which is pressing for early repayment of Pounds 70m
mezzanine debt.
The debt was provided in 1989 to finance the management buy-out of Magnet.
GE is claiming that it was misled over the conditions under which the loan
was made.
