<HEADLINE>
FT  03 FEB 92 / Council venture capital rises
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By CHARLES BATCHELOR
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
LOCAL-AUTHORITY pension funds have become the largest source of venture
capital available in the regions, according to a survey.
Over the past two years to the end of last year they have increased their
investment in venture capital by 51 per cent, according to Pensions
Investment Research Consultants (PIRC).
While the venture capital industry has experienced a general slowdown in
rates of growth, the pension funds increased their investment by Pounds 92m
to Pounds 271m.
PIRC, which advises local authorities on investments, found that a total of
62 local-authority pension funds, 63 per cent of the total, had made venture
capital investments.
Of the pension funds surveyed, 41 per cent said they expected to increase
the sums allocated for venture capital.
Forty-two pension funds had allocated up to 1 per cent of their assets to
venture capital; 10 had allocated up to 2 per cent; five had allocated up to
5 per cent and one had allocated more than 5 per cent. The legal maximum for
pension funds is 10 per cent.
Local Authority Pension Fund Venture Capital Investment. PIRC, 40 Bowling
Green Lane, London EC1R 0NE.
</TEXT>
